{"id":"project-LICHEN-hotd","title":"ctx_find_by_recipient_locked crashes on NULL recipient_id with nonzero len","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/oscore/oscore.c
Lines: 58-62

The internal function ctx_find_by_recipient_locked does not validate that recipient_id is non-NULL before memcpy:

```c
uint8_t padded_input[OSCORE_ID_MAX_LEN] = {0};
if (recipient_id_len <= OSCORE_ID_MAX_LEN) {
    memcpy(padded_input, recipient_id, recipient_id_len);  // Crash if recipient_id NULL
}
```

If recipient_id is NULL but recipient_id_len > 0, memcpy causes undefined behavior (likely crash).

While this is an internal function, its callers (oscore_ctx_lookup and oscore_ctx_get) do not validate recipient_id before calling. The public API allows:
```c
oscore_ctx_get(NULL, 5, &ctx_out);  // Will crash
```

Fix: Add validation in the public API functions:
```c
if (recipient_id == NULL && recipient_id_len > 0) {
    return OSCORE_ERR_INVALID_PARAM;
}
```

Or in the internal function:
```c
if (recipient_id_len <= OSCORE_ID_MAX_LEN && recipient_id != NULL) {
    memcpy(padded_input, recipient_id, recipient_id_len);
}
